UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jmcb.12901
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract I show that adding an overlapping generations structure to the canonical New Keynesian model can generate an optimal inflation rate that is significantly positive. In a baseline calibration of the model, the optimal inflation target is comprised between 0.8% and 3.2% in annual terms. In this framework, deviations from long-run price stability are optimal because the rate at which firms discount future profit flows naturally differs from the rate at which the planner discounts future utility flows.
ER  - 

